<paragraph blockId="9.[106,745,151,1820]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">
This is one of the most confused of the Brongniart fossil-taxa, and is still regularly used for both fern and seedplant fossil-species. However, the 
<typeStatus box="[476,522,378,402]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="STERNBERG" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="BRONGNIART" box="[539,647,377,401]" class="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (unclassified foliage)" family="Pteridophytes/Pteridosperms (awaiting allocation)" genus="Filicites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (awaiting allocation)" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[539,647,377,401]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">S. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is welldocumented as a Mississippian-age early seed-plant (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kidston, R." box="[106,259,442,466]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 670" refId="ref18508" refString="Kidston, R. (1923 - 1925): Fossil plants of the Carboniferous rocks of Great Britain. - Memoirs of the Geological Survey of Great Britain, Palaeontology, 2: 1 - 670." type="journal article" year="1923">Kidston 1923</bibRefCitation>
-1925: 242) and so the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sternberg" authorityYear="1825" box="[605,744,442,466]" class="Pteridospermopsida" family="Lyginopteridaceae" genus="Sphenopteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lyginopteridales" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[605,744,442,466]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Sphenopteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should only be applied to this group of early seed-plant fronds. It should be noted in passing that Kidston adopted for this species the taxonomic synonym 
<emphasis box="[613,745,538,562]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Diplotmema</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(SCHLOTHEIM ex POTONIE) GOTHAN, 1913" authorityName="GOTHAN" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="SCHLOTHEIM ex POTONIE" box="[106,706,571,595]" class="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (unclassified foliage)" family="Pteridophytes/Pteridosperms (awaiting allocation)" genus="Filicites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (awaiting allocation)" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adiantioides">
<emphasis box="[106,238,571,595]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">adiantioides</emphasis>
(SCHLOTHEIM ex POTONIÉ) 
<bibRefCitation author="Gothan, W." box="[547,706,571,595]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 278" refId="ref17867" refString="Gothan, W. (1913): Die oberschlesische Steinkohlenflora. 1 Teil. - Abhandlungen der Koniglich Preussischen Geologischen Landesanstalt, Neue Folge, 75: 1 - 278." type="journal article" year="1913">GOTHAN, 1913</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<emphasis box="[106,257,603,626]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Cuneatopteris</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="SCHLOTHEIM ex POTONIE, 1907, p. 2" authorityName="POTONIE" authorityPageNumber="2" authorityYear="1907" class="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (unclassified foliage)" family="Pteridophytes/Pteridosperms (awaiting allocation)" genus="Filicites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (awaiting allocation)" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adiantoides">
<emphasis box="[269,393,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">adiantoides</emphasis>
SCHLOTHEIM ex 
<bibRefCitation author="Potonie, H." box="[581,741,603,627]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" refId="ref19941" refString="Potonie, H. (1907): Abbildungen und Beschreibungen fossiler Pflanzen-Reste, Lieferung 5, Nr. 81: Cuneatopteris. - Koniglich Preussische Geologische Landesanstalt, Berlin, 2 pp." type="book" year="1907">POTONIÉ, 1907</bibRefCitation>
, p. 2
</taxonomicName>
) since the first use of the species epithet (as “ 
<taxonomicName authority="&quot; SCHLOTHEIM, 1820" authorityName="SCHLOTHEIM" authorityYear="1820" class="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (unclassified foliage)" family="Pteridophytes/Pteridosperms (awaiting allocation)" genus="Filicites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (awaiting allocation)" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adiantoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Filicites adiantoides</emphasis>
” 
<bibRefCitation author="Schlotheim, E. F. von" box="[248,439,667,691]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" refId="ref20364" refString="Schlotheim, E. F. von (1820): Die Petrefactenkunde auf ihrem jetzigen Standpunkte durch die Beschreibung seiner Sammlung versteinerter und fossiler Uberreste des Thier- und Pflanzenreichs der Vorwelt erlautert. - Becker, Gotha, 437 pp." type="book" year="1820">SCHLOTHEIM, 1820</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) pre-dated both Brongniart’s and Sternberg’s works. However, as “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="GOTHAN" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="SCHLOTHEIM ex POTONIE" box="[521,682,700,724]" class="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (unclassified foliage)" family="Pteridophytes/Pteridosperms (awaiting allocation)" genus="Filicites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (awaiting allocation)" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adiantioides">
<emphasis box="[521,682,700,724]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">F. adiantioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” was published prior to the starting point for publication of fossiltaxa (ICN, Art. 13.1) this must be rejected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[106,745,151,1820]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">
This raises a practical problem with classifying some fossil fern fronds with small lobed pinnules, especially of Palaeozoic age. Although there are numerous welldefined fossil-genera for such ferns (e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="ZEILLER, 1883" authorityName="ZEILLER" authorityYear="1883" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Renaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Marattiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[546,650,893,917]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Renaultia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zeiller, R." pageId="9" pageNumber="18" pagination="177 - 209" refId="ref21541" refString="Zeiller, R. (1883): Fructifications de fougeres du terrain houiller. - Annales des Sciences Naturelles, 6 e Serie, Botanique, 16: 177 - 209." type="journal article" year="1883">ZEILLER, 1883</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="KIDSTON, 1884" authorityName="KIDSTON" authorityYear="1884" box="[181,453,925,949]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Zeilleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Marattiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[181,273,925,949]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Zeilleria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kidston, R." box="[289,453,925,949]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" pagination="590 - 598" refId="ref18431" refString="Kidston, R. (1884): On the fructification of Zeilleria (Sphenopteris) delicatula, Sternb., sp.; with remarks on Urnatopteris (Sphenopteris) tenella, Brongt., and Hymenophyllites (Sphenopteris) quadridactylites, Gutbier, sp. - Quarterly Journal of the Geological Society, 40: 590 - 598. https: // doi. org / 10.1144 / GSL. JGS. 1884.40.01 - 04.49" type="journal article" year="1884">KIDSTON, 1884</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) these are diagnosed by their reproductive structures. Those species for which reproductive structures are unknown have tended to be placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sternberg" authorityYear="1825" box="[216,355,1022,1046]" class="Pteridospermopsida" family="Lyginopteridaceae" genus="Sphenopteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lyginopteridales" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[216,355,1022,1046]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Sphenopteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Brousmiche, C." box="[423,617,1022,1046]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" refId="ref16362" refString="Brousmiche, C. (1983): Les fougeres sphenopteridiennes du bassin houiller Sarro-Lorrain (2 vols) (Publication no. 10). - Societe Geologique du Nord, Lille, 480 pp. + 100 pls." type="book" year="1983">Brousmiche 1983</bibRefCitation>
) but this is not tenable given that the 
<typeStatus box="[387,433,1055,1079]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
of that name is a seed-plant. There is in fact no available legitimate name for a fossilgenus of species of such fern fossils for which reproductive structures are unknown. It would be possible to establish an “artificial” genus for such species; this would be analogous to the fossil-genus 
<taxonomicName authority="BRONGNIART, 1828 a" authorityName="BRONGNIART" authorityYear="1828" box="[324,679,1215,1239]" genus="Taeniopteris" kingdom="Plantae" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,456,1216,1239]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Taeniopteris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brongniart, A." box="[468,679,1215,1239]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 223" refId="ref15409" refString="Brongniart, A. (1828 a): Prodrome d'une Histoire des vegetaux fossiles. F. G. Levrault, Paris and Strasbourg, 223 pp [also published in Dictionnaire des sciences naturelles, 57: 1 - 223]." type="book chapter" year="1828">BRONGNIART, 1828a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
nom. cons., which is now used for entire cycadophyte-like leaves for which neither cuticles nor reproductive structures are known (van Konijnenburg-van Cittert et al. 2017). However, to date no such fossil-genus has been established for these fern fossils.Another option would be to revert to 
<bibRefCitation author="Brongniart, A." pageId="9" pageNumber="18" pagination="203 - 240" refId="ref15150" refString="Brongniart, A. (1822 a): Sur la classification et la distribution des vegetaux fossiles en general, et sur ceux des terrains de sediment superieur en particulier. Introduction, Chapitre I. - Memoires du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, 8: 203 - 240, pls 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1822">Brongniart’s (1822a)</bibRefCitation>
original conception for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sternberg" authorityYear="1825" box="[440,579,1409,1433]" class="Pteridospermopsida" family="Lyginopteridaceae" genus="Sphenopteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lyginopteridales" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[440,579,1409,1433]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Sphenopteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as including all pteridophyllous foliage with lobed pinnules and supressing names such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ZEILLER" authorityYear="1883" box="[269,373,1473,1497]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Renaultia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Marattiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[269,373,1473,1497]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Renaultia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="KIDSTON" authorityYear="1884" box="[427,519,1473,1497]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marattiaceae" genus="Zeilleria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Marattiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[427,519,1473,1497]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Zeilleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but this would seem a retrograde step. The only viable option within the current framework of the ICN is to make a judgement as to the taxonomic position of such species based on similarities in the morphology of the sterile foliage, maybe using an open-nomenclature-like qualifier similar to that used in palaeozoology (
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, S. C." box="[275,445,1667,1691]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" pagination="713 - 719" refId="ref19758" refString="Matthews, S. C. (1973): Notes on open nomenclature and on synonymy lists. - Palaeontology, 16: 713 - 719." type="journal article" year="1973">Matthews 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bengtson, P." box="[455,620,1667,1691]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" pagination="223 - 227" refId="ref15058" refString="Bengtson, P. (1988): Open nomenclature. - Palaeontology, 31: 223 - 227." type="journal article" year="1988">Bengtson 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[106,745,151,1820]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">
In passing, mention should be made of a later homonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="STERNBERG" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="BRONGNIART" box="[136,244,1731,1755]" class="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (unclassified foliage)" family="Pteridophytes/Pteridosperms (awaiting allocation)" genus="Filicites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pteridophyta/Pteridospermophyta (awaiting allocation)" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[136,244,1731,1755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">S. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(YOKOYAMA) OISI, 1940" authorityName="OISI" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="YOKOYAMA" box="[259,744,1731,1758]" class="Pteridospermopsida" family="Lyginopteridaceae" genus="Sphenopteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lyginopteridales" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[259,487,1731,1755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Sphenopteris elegans</emphasis>
(YOKOYAMA) ÔISI, 1940
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName authority="YOKOYAMA, 1895" authorityName="YOKOYAMA" authorityYear="1895" box="[139,555,1763,1787]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dicksoniaceae" genus="Onychiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cyatheales" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[139,361,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Onychiopsis elegans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yokoyama, M." box="[370,555,1763,1787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18" pagination="201 - 231" refId="ref21502" refString="Yokoyama, M. (1895): Mesozoic plants from Kozuke, Kii, Awa, and Tosa. - Journal of the College of Science, Imperial University, Japan, 7: 201 - 231." type="journal article" year="1895">YOKOYAMA, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) based on a 
<typeStatus box="[699,745,1764,1788]" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
from the Lower Cretaceous Series of 
<collectingCountry box="[506,570,1796,1819]" name="Japan" pageId="9" pageNumber="18">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
